{
  "name": "NAUClassSearchOntology",
  "description": "Grounded ontology for the NAU Class Search Data Agent. Internal RDF identifiers are kept stable so the ontology playground preserves the graph connections, while entity display titles use underscores and relationship labels read as natural language. The model separates Course from Course_Offering, models Course_Offering as subject plus catalog number, places prerequisites and requisites on Course_Offering, separates Term from Session, models multiple Sessions per Term with week lengths, connects Buildings to Campus and Campus to College, and models Class_Section enrollment through Academic_Policy and Reserve_Capacity_Rule.",
  "icon": "📦",
  "category": "other",
  "tags": [],
  "author": ""
}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rdf:RDF
    xml:base="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/"
    xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
    xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
    xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
    xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
    xmlns:ont="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/">

    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/">
        <rdfs:label>NAUClassSearchOntology</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Grounded ontology for the NAU Class Search Data Agent. Internal RDF identifiers are kept stable so the ontology playground preserves the graph connections, while entity display titles use underscores and relationship labels read as natural language. The model separates Course from Course_Offering, models Course_Offering as subject plus catalog number, places prerequisites and requisites on Course_Offering, separates Term from Session, models multiple Sessions per Term with week lengths, connects Buildings to Campus and Campus to College, and models Class_Section enrollment through Academic_Policy and Reserve_Capacity_Rule.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>

    <!-- ===================== -->
    <!-- Entity Types (Classes) -->
    <!-- ===================== -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/Course">
        <rdfs:label>Course</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Catalog-level academic course concept grounded in course catalog data. A Course represents the stable academic idea, including title, units, career, level, and long catalog description text. Specific offerable variants, subject/catalog-number combinations, course_offer_number, and requisite logic are modeled through Course_Offering.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🎓</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#2F80ED</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/CourseOffering">
        <rdfs:label>Course_Offering</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Offerable course concept grounded in the PeopleSoft course_id + course_offer_number pattern. A Course_Offering is made up of a Subject and catalog_number, belongs to a parent Course, can be scheduled as Class_Sections, and is the correct place to attach prerequisite, co-requisite, placement, equivalency, and recommended preparation rules.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🧾</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#6C63FF</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/Subject">
        <rdfs:label>Subject</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Academic subject code such as CS, BIO, MATH, PSY, or EE. A Subject is mapped to an Academic_Organization and College so class search can reason from subject area to academic ownership.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🔤</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#1ABC9C</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/College">
        <rdfs:label>College</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>College-level academic grouping. A College can contain multiple Academic_Organizations and can own or be associated with Subjects.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🏫</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#F2A541</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/ClassSection">
        <rdfs:label>Class_Section</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Scheduled class section grounded in class scheduling data. A Class_Section is the student-facing scheduled instance of a Course_Offering in a specific Session, with enrollment, capacity, status, delivery mode, class number, multiple Meeting_Patterns, instructors, Reserve_Capacity_Rules, and Academic_Policy controls for add, drop, and waitlist timing.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🗓️</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#00A6ED</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/Term">
        <rdfs:label>Term</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Academic term such as Fall, Spring, or Summer. A Term is measured in number of weeks and can contain multiple Sessions. For example, a Summer Term may be 12 weeks while it contains multiple 5-week summer sessions.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>📅</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#00B894</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/Session">
        <rdfs:label>Session</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Session within a Term, such as a 12-week summer session, 5-week summer session 1, 5-week summer session 2, or 5-week summer session 3. Each Session is measured in number of weeks and can contain multiple Class_Sections.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>⏱️</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#20C997</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/EnrollmentDateRule">
        <rdfs:label>Academic_Policy</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Academic policy governing Class_Section enrollment timing and rules, including open enrollment, add/drop periods, waitlist policy, withdrawal deadlines, and related session or section-specific controls.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🚦</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#FF8C42</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/ProfessorInstructor">
        <rdfs:label>Instructor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Professor or instructor assigned to teach a Class_Section. Uses EMPLID or another person identifier as the stable natural key and instructor_name as the display value.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>👩‍🏫</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#9B51E0</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/AcademicOrganization">
        <rdfs:label>Academic_Organization</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Academic owner such as college, division, department, school, or academic organization. Supports questions by organization, subject ownership, class ownership, and program ownership.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🏛️</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#F2994A</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/MeetingPattern">
        <rdfs:label>Meeting_Pattern</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Meeting days, meeting times, and location pattern for a Class_Section. A Class_Section can have multiple Meeting_Patterns for lecture, lab, fieldwork, or other components.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🕒</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#27AE60</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/FacilityRoom">
        <rdfs:label>Room</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Physical room or facility where a Meeting_Pattern occurs. A Facility_Room is located in a Building.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🚪</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#56CCF2</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/Building">
        <rdfs:label>Building</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Campus building that contains one or more Facility_Rooms. A Building is located on a Campus.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🏢</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#828282</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/Campus">
        <rdfs:label>Campus</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Campus or location context for Buildings and Class_Sections, such as the Flagstaff Mountain Campus. A Campus belongs to a College in this ontology design.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🌲</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#145A32</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/ReserveCapacityRule">
        <rdfs:label>Reserve_Capacity_Rule</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Reserve capacity rule that allows eligible student populations to enroll in a Class_Section. A Class_Section can have multiple Reserve_Capacity_Rules with reserved seats, eligible populations, consent requirements, and enrollment counts.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🔐</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#EB5757</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/ClassAttribute">
        <rdfs:label>Class_Attribute</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Attribute attached to a Class_Section or Course_Offering, such as Liberal Studies, CCAT, component, lecture, lab, fieldwork, or other designations.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🏷️</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#F2C94C</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/RequisiteRule">
        <rdfs:label>Requisite_Rule</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Prerequisite, co-requisite, equivalency, placement, or recommended preparation rule. Requisite_Rules attach to Course_Offerings and point to prerequisite Course_Offerings, which avoids a direct Course-to-Course loop.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🔗</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#BB6BD9</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/AcademicProgram">
        <rdfs:label>Academic_Program</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Degree, plan, certificate, or academic program that contains Academic_Requirements and may require Courses or Course_Offerings.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>🎯</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#219653</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology/nauclasssearchontology/AcademicRequirement">
        <rdfs:label>Academic_Requirement</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Requirement inside an Academic_Program, such as capstone, lab science, Liberal Studies, major requirement, or prerequisite-ready pathway. Requirements may be satisfied by Courses or Course_Offerings.</rdfs:comment>
        <ont:icon>✅</ont:icon>
        <ont:color>#2D9CDB</ont:color>
    </owl:Class>

